330
00:19:24,360 --> 00:19:27,600
# There's no chance for us

331
00:19:29,880 --> 00:19:33,280
# It's all decided for us...

332
00:19:33,280 --> 00:19:35,960
Within the past half hour, we've
heard that the film star

333
00:19:35,960 --> 00:19:39,840
Rock Hudson has died at his home
in California. He was 59.

334
00:19:39,840 --> 00:19:44,720
Rock Hudson dying actually did
affect Freddie.

335
00:19:46,560 --> 00:19:49,840
REPORTER:  News cameras were kept at
a distance as the body was moved

336
00:19:49,840 --> 00:19:52,280
into the coroner's van,
but there was trouble with two

337
00:19:52,280 --> 00:19:54,440
photographers for two
London newspapers.

338
00:19:54,440 --> 00:19:58,480
They were trying to get shots
of the body inside the van.

339
00:19:58,480 --> 00:20:05,240
# Who dares to love forever

340
00:20:05,240 --> 00:20:09,680
Hollywood is full of anxious people.
The scourge of Aids, especially

341
00:20:09,680 --> 00:20:12,400
of Rock Hudson's, has cut
through the old myths

342
00:20:12,400 --> 00:20:14,960
about everlasting youth and beauty.

343
00:20:14,960 --> 00:20:17,600
# Forever

344
00:20:17,600 --> 00:20:24,200
It made Freddie face the fact
that instead of us being immortal

345
00:20:24,200 --> 00:20:26,840
and it happening to someone else,

346
00:20:26,840 --> 00:20:30,240
it was getting closer and closer
to home.

347
00:20:30,240 --> 00:20:33,600
# Who waits forever anyway? #

348
00:20:36,920 --> 00:20:39,840
CHEERING AND APPLAUSE

349
00:20:48,480 --> 00:20:51,640
ROGER TAYLOR:  Well, we did two
